Countertops have even started taking the main stage as a statement piece in the kitchenyet another reason why purchasing the right type of countertop is so essential!</p>

3404 <p>To choose the best countertop for your kitchen or other room in your house, here is a guide about the best kitchen countertop materials and how to coordinate them with your chosen aesthetic.</p>

3491 <h2>What to Consider When Purchasing Countertops</h2>

3492 </div>

3493 </div>

3494 </div>

3496 <div>

3497 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-ad-dc-c-b-fbbdf">

3529 <div>

3530 <p>Heres what you should consider and look for while searching for durable countertop materials:</p>

3531 <ul>

3532 <li>Stain resistance</li>

3533 <li>Heat resistance</li>

3534 <li>Scratch &amp; chip resistance</li>

3535 <li>Easy maintenance</li>

3536 <li>Appearance &amp; beauty</li>

3537 <li>Price</li>

3538 </ul>

3539 <p>Depending on the material, the countertop may require varying degrees of maintenance from regular cleaning tips and sealing. Different types of kitchen countertops may be prone or resistant to scratches, heat distortion or scalding, color fading, or absorption of fluids, which can lead to discoloration and stains. Knowing such things can help you pick the best kitchen countertop material that fits your functional and lifestyle needs.</p>

3540 <p>On top of being durable and easy to maintain, you likely want your countertops to look good within your kitchen too! That means coordinating the countertop style and color with flooring, cabinet and

3541 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/cabinet-materials/" target="_blank">cabinet materials</a>, hardware, and other features to achieve your desired aesthetic.

3542 </p>

3543 <p>Like most other home features, you get what you pay for, so the more inexpensive the countertop material, the quality may also reflect that price point, and vice versa for more lofty price tags. Sometimes paying more upfront for countertop materials can save money in maintenance or replacement costs later on.</p>

3641 <span style="font-size: 16px;">

3642 <strong>Pros</strong>

3655 <br> Resistant to scratches and stains

3656 <br> Resists mold, mildew, and bacteria

3657 <br> Doesnt require sealing

3658 <br> Longevity

3659 <br> Low maintenance &amp; easy to clean

3660 <br> Great for kitchens and bathrooms

3678 <h4>

3679 <span style="font-size: 16px;">

3680 <strong>Cons</strong>

3681 </span>

3682 </h4>

3683 </div>

3684 </div>

3685 </div>

3686 </div>

3687 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-ab-fb-c-bd-edc">

3688 <div>

3690 <div>

3691 <p> Prone to heat damage or melting

3692 <br> Can be scratched

3693 <br> Direct sunlight can fade color

3694 </p>

3695 </div>

3696 </div>

3697 </div>

3710 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

3711 <div>

3712 <p>One of the most popular and best kitchen countertop materials is quartz, or engineered stone. Quartz is incredibly sturdy and resistant to many of the issues that may plague other countertop materials, making it hygienic and easy to maintain.</p>

3713 <p>When most designers say quartz countertops, they are not 100% solid quartzite (which would be very high maintenance). Rather, quartz countertops are usually in the 90% range of pure quartz combined with other resins or composites to create a gorgeous, durable, non-porous surface for your countertops.</p>

3734 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-f----abea">

3740 <h4>

3741 <span style="font-size: 18px;">

3742 <strong>Maintenance</strong>

3743 </span>

3744 </h4>

3745 </div>

3746 </div>

3747 </div>

3748 </div>

3749 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-f-ef-fe-be-bffccdd">

3751 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

3752 <div>

3753 <p>Caring for quartz countertops is incredibly simple as they are one of the more low-maintenance countertop options available. Soap and water should do the trick. No sealing necessary.</p>

3754 </div>

3970 <p>One of the most popular countertop materials, granite is a highly desirable countertop material for its durability, hardiness, and distinct appearance.</p>

3971 <p>Due to granites popularity, its more widely available and more affordable than it used to be, though its still on the upper end of the spectrum since its natural stone.</p>

3998 <p>

3999 <span style="font-size: 18px;">

4000 <strong>Maintenance</strong>

4001 </span>

4002 </p>

4003 </div>

4004 </div>

4005 </div>

4007 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-fe-ab-f-bce-fffbb">

4008 <div>

4009 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

4010 <div>

4011 <p>Natural stone countertops, whether granite, marble, or other stone,

4012 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/care-for-stone-countertops/" target="_blank">require regular maintenance and care</a>. Granite is a porous stone, so it requires regular sealing. Depending on the strength of the sealant applied, a new sealant might need to be applied every 1-5 years. With proper care and sealing, granite can last decades.

4013 </p>

4014 <p>Some granite countertops will come professionally sealed and will likely not need sealing for up to several years. Sensa granite countertops are sealed with a proprietary protective coating that doesnt require annual sealing.</p>

4015 </div>

4053 <div>

4054 <p>Granite comes in a wide variety of colors and patterns, so its easy to personalize with your cabinets and flooring. Keep in mind that granite countertops can also feature multiple color tones, so pay attention to the shades to create the aesthetic you want.</p>

4055 <p>This in-demand stone can work with just about any style depending on the grain and colors. Its about coordinating similar or contrasting colors to pair countertops with cabinets and flooring.</p>

4056 <p>For example, black granite countertops pair very well with white cabinets to create a beautiful contrast in modern styles. Black granite countertops also have a home in traditional and rustic styles when paired with

4057 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/wood-kitchen-cabinet-types/" target="_blank">wood kitchen cabinets</a> or other organic elements.

4227 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

4228 <div>

4229 <p>A very trendy and beautiful countertop material, marble countertops are another desirable natural stone option on the high-end side. Marble comes in two forms: honed and polished. Honed marble is porous and has a matte appearance, where polished marble has a protective surface with a shiny sheen.</p>

4230 <p>One way to reduce the cost of marble countertops is to use marble tiles instead of slabs.</p>

4765 <p>For a lower-maintenance natural stone, look at beautiful slate (in tiles to get more bang for your buck).</p>

5202 <p>Another fairly affordable countertop material is butcher block, which can be applied to one section of your countertop or the whole of your base cabinetry layout, depending on the functionality you want in your kitchen counter.</p>

5203 <p>Butcher blocks are often composed of natural wood slabs like maple, oak, teak, ash, or even bambooeach of which comes with their own unique appearance and properties.</p>

5204 <p>Butcher block can come sealed or unsealed, however, sealed butcher block isnt recommended for bare food prep due to chemicals in the sealant.</p>

5441 <div>

5442 <p> Requires regular waxing and sealing

5443 <br> Prone to scratches

5444 <br> Not resistant to stains

5445 </p>

5446 </div>

5447 </div>

5448 </div>

5449 </div>

5461 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5462 <div>

5463 <p>Concrete countertops have become more trendy and stylish as of late. Poured, set, and sealed into the shape of your desired countertop, concrete or cement countertops can incorporate pigments or other materials like glass mixed in to create a unique look in your kitchen. Since concrete is very heavy once it is set, its handmade to the customers needs.</p>

5575 <div>

5576 <h2>Cost of Countertops</h2>

5577 </div>

5578 </div>

5579 </div>

5580 </div>

5581 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-dbe-cf-f-ab-dbdc">

5582 <div>

5583 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5584 <div>

5585 <p>Depending on the material, countertops may cost between $20 - $300 per square foot, with luxury natural stones at the top range (like lava rock) and materials like laminate and tile at the lower end of the spectrum.</p>

5586 <p>Its not only the material that will determine how much your investment will be in your countertop renovation. Here are other accompanying factors will affect the cost of new countertops:</p>

5587 <ul>

5588 <li>Amount and thickness of countertop material</li>

5589 <li>Installation and labor</li>

5590 <li>Custom countertop shapes or designs</li>

5591 <li>Removal of existing countertops</li>

5592 </ul>

5593 </div>

5594 </div>

5595 </div>

5596 </div>

5597 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-fc-d-c-bc-fdea">

5598 <div>

5599 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5600 <div>

5601 <p>With this in mind, you can plan for a budget that allows you to purchase a durable and beautiful countertop that you can stay on top of maintaining.</p>
